Privacy Policy for Money Merge 2048 Deluxe Game
 Privacy Policy describes how we (Green Quark Developer Studio) handle information in connection with your use of the "Money Merge 2048 Deluxe" mobile game.
Our Commitment to Your Privacy We are committed to protecting your privacy. We want you to understand how any data is handled when you play Money Merge 2048 Deluxe.
Data We DO NOT Collect Directly We, the developers of Money Merge 2048 Deluxe, do not directly collect, store, or process any personal data from you, such as your name, email address, location, or any other personally identifiable information. Your gameplay data, progress, and scores are generally stored locally on your device unless specific Google services (like Google Play Games Services) are utilized for features like cloud saves, leaderboards, or achievements (see below).
Data Collected by Third-Party Services (Google) Our game integrates with services provided by Google, which may collect data in accordance with their own privacy policies. These services are essential for the game's functionality, performance, and to support the free-to-play model:
Google Play Services: This includes services like Google Play Games Services (for achievements, leaderboards, and cloud save functionality, if implemented). Google may collect device information, account identifiers (non-personally identifiable to us), and usage data to provide these services.
Advertising (e.g., Google AdMob): As a free game, Money Merge 2048 Deluxe may display advertisements provided by Google AdMob. To deliver relevant ads and measure their performance, Google AdMob may collect certain non-personal data, such as:
Device Identifiers: Such as advertising IDs (e.g., Android Advertising ID).
Device Information: Such as device type, operating system, and language settings.
Usage Data: Such as interactions with ads.
This data is used by Google to personalize ads, cap frequency, report on ad campaigns, and detect fraud. We do not have direct access to this data in a personally identifiable form.
Analytics and Crash Reporting (e.g., Google Analytics for Firebase, Firebase Crashlytics): To understand game performance, identify bugs, and improve the user experience, we may use Google's analytics and crash reporting tools. These tools may collect aggregated, anonymized data about game usage, device information, and crash reports. This data helps us improve the game and does not identify you personally.
How Third Parties Use Data The third-party services mentioned above collect and use data according to their respective privacy policies. We encourage you to review Google's privacy policy for more detailed information on their data handling practices:
Google Privacy Policy
Data Security While we do not directly collect personal data, we strive to ensure that any data processed by integrated third-party services is handled with appropriate security measures.
Children's Privacy Money Merge 2048 Deluxe is not intended for children under the age of [e.g., 13, or applicable age in your region]. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children under [e.g., 13]. If we become aware that we have inadvertently received personal data from a child under [e.g., 13], we will delete such information from our records.
Changes to This Privacy Policy We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy here. We advise you to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.
Contact Us If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at: Support Email Address - e.g., quantunnels@gmail.com
